<div class="subscribe-container">
  <h1 class="subscribe-header">Weekend coffee with Bitcoin - an article a day!</h1>
  <h3 class="subscribe-header">Sign-up to get a curated list of the best essays and most relevant news item to your inbox.</h3><br>
  <p class="subscribe-para">Seven essays a week, an article a day to keep you on top of the crypto world. After all, you have a role to play in the new brave world of decentralized economy.
<br>The world of blockchain and Crypto currency is growing every day. There is a lot of content out there. But, noise to signal ratio is extremely high.
<br>We are a group of crypto nerds who are deep into the world. Help us mine the gem for you.
<br>Sign-up for the weekly newsletter to stay on top of the crypto world.</p>
  <div class="subscribe-para">
  <br>
    <p>
      <%= text_field_tag 'search', nil, placeholder: 'Email Address', class: "subscribe-text" %>
    </p>
    <p>
      <br>
      <%= button_tag "Subscribe now",class:"subscribe-button"%>
    </p>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="sub-news-container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="sub-news-head">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        Trending News
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        Editor's Choice 
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        Latest Tweets
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="sub-news-block">
        <% @posts.each do |post| %>
          <p class="subscribe-news">
            <% if post['thread']['main_image'] %>
              <%= link_to image_tag("#{post['thread']['main_image']}", class: "sub-image"), "#{post['url']}", target: :_blank, class: "sub-image"%>
            <% else %>
              <%= link_to image_tag("bitcoins-default.jpg", class: "sub-image"), "#{post['url']}", target: :_blank %>
            <% end %>
            <%= link_to post['title'], "#{post['url']}", target: :_blank %>
          </p>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="sub-news-block">
        <%= link_to "A hacker stole $31M of Ether — how it happened, and what it means for Ethereum", "https://medium.freecodecamp.org/a-hacker-stole-31m-of-ether-how-it-happened-and-what-it-means-for-ethereum-9e5dc29e33ce" %>
        <p class="editors-para">Yesterday, a hacker pulled off the second biggest heist in the history of digital currencies. <br>
        Around 12:00 PST, an unknown attacker exploited a critical flaw in the Parity multi-signature wallet on the Ethereum network, draining three massive wallets of over $31,000,000 worth of Ether in a matter of minutes. Given a couple more hours, the hacker could’ve made off with over $180,000,000 from vulnerable wallets... <%= link_to "continue reading...","https://medium.freecodecamp.org/a-hacker-stole-31m-of-ether-how-it-happened-and-what-it-means-for-ethereum-9e5dc29e33ce"%></p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="col-md-4">
      <div class="sub-news-block">
      <a class="twitter-timeline"
      href="https://twitter.com/Bitcoinnews6"
      data-tweet-limit="2">Bitcoin Twitter</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>




